<% content_for(:page_title, 'Style Guide') %>

<div class="page-title">
  <h1>
    Style Guide
  </h1>
</div>

<p class="lead">Transition’s UI is powered by <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/">bootstrap 3.1</a>, using <a href="https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass/tree/v3.1.0">bootstrap SASS</a> v3.1.0 (<a href="https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass/blob/v3.1.0/vendor/assets/stylesheets/bootstrap/_mixins.scss">mixins</a>), but maintaining bootstrap 2 button styles. This guide documents how transition is using bootstrap, where the app has diverged from default styles and any custom styles needed to fill in the gaps.</p>

<h2>Grid</h2>
<p class="lead">Transition uses the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#grid">default bootstrap</a> <strong>12 column scaleable responsive grid</strong>.</p>
<div class="row add-bottom-margin">
  <div class="grid-example col-md-2">col-md-2</div>
  <div class="grid-example col-md-4">col-md-4</div>
  <div class="grid-example col-md-6">col-md-6</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="grid-example col-md-12">col-md-12</div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Buttons</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Despite using bootstrap 3 transition uses the classic bootstrap button styles for consistency with other admin apps and for improved usability. The source to override the buttons with the originals is from <a href="https://gist.github.com/Erve1879/6167373">https://gist.github.com/Erve1879/6167373</a>.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Default</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Primary</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-success">Success</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info">Info</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-warning">Warning</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-danger">Danger</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-link">Link</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Create and success actions use <code>btn-success</code>.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-success">
      Save mapping
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">When adding an item include an <code>icon-plus</code> icon.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-default">
      <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i> Add mapping
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Page headers with subtitles</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Page headers have a single pixel bottom-border. Subtitles - if used - run underneath this.</p>
  <section class="headers col-md-6">
    <header>
      <div class="page-title">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="#">BIS</a></p>

      <div class="page-title with-border">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="#">BIS</a></p>

    </header>
  </section>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Tables</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>When using a table with two layers of headings, usually for interacting with table content, <code>table-header</code> and <code>table-header-secondary</code> classes are used.</p>

    <p>The second example shows a table with selectable rows. Selected rows highlight in yellow. The checkbox in the header selects all rows.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="col-md-6">
    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th>Secondary header</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>

    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover" data-module="selectable-table">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th></th>
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th class="selectable-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <label>
                <input type="checkbox" class="js-toggle-all" />
              </label>
            </div>
          </th>
          <th><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Action</a></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="selected-row">
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="js-toggle-row" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Selected row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>

    <script>GOVUK.SelectableTable.setup();</script>
  </ul>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Links</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>To match bootstrap’s muted text, a muted link class is available.</p>
    <p>Transition has also added purple <code>:visited</code> styles. These apply to the main content but not to buttons.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="col-md-6">
    <a href="/style" class="link-muted">Muted link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style">Visited link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>">Normal link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style" class="btn btn-default">Visited button link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style" class="btn btn-success">Another visited button link</a><br><br>
  </ul>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Tags</h2>
<div class="row add-bottom-margin">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>Tags are metadata added to mappings. They are white with a blue border, purposefully set back from the main content so they don’t impede the scanning of paths.</p>
    <p>When they are links they have the usual visited link styles. They should also use the <code>rel="tag"</code> attribute.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <span class="tag">tag as a span</span><br />
    <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tag as a link</a><br />
    <a href="/style" class="tag" rel="tag">tag as a visited link</a><br />
    <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">many</a> <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tags</a> <a href="#" class="tag" rel="tag">in a</a> <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">row</a> <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">and one</a> <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">of them</a> <a href="/style" class="tag" rel="tag">is visited</a><br />
    <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">A very long tag. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>Include a <code>glyphicon-remove</code> icon for dismissible tags.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> dismissible tag</a> <a href="#" class="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> another dismissible tag</a> <a href="#" class="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> this tag should go</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>Tags can be wrapped in a list using the <code>tag-list</code> class.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <ul class="tag-list">
      <li>
       <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tags in a list</a>
      </li>
      <li>
       <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">this tag is in an li</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>Tags can be used in all shapes and sizes.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h1>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tag in an h1</a>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> tag in an h1</a>
    </h1>
    <h2>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tag in an h2</a>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> tag in an h2</a>
    </h2>
    <h3>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag">tag in an h3</a>
      <a href="#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>" class="tag" rel="tag"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> tag in an h3</a>
    </h3>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Tagging</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="lead col-md-6">
    Tags are entered as a comma separated list when JavaScript is disabled. With JavaScript input is progressively enhanced using the <a href="http://ivaynberg.github.io/select2/">Select2 library</a> and <a href="https://github.com/argerim/select2-rails">gem</a>. Tags can be individually removed and autocompleted, and it’s clearer how tags are separated.
  </p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <label for="plain-tag-list">Without JavaScript</label>
    <input id="plain-tag-list" type="text" class="form-control add-bottom-margin" />

    <label for="empty-tag-list">Empty tag list</label>
    <input id="empty-tag-list" type="text" class="form-control js-tag-list add-bottom-margin" />

    <label for="filled-tag-list">Pre-filled tag list</label>
    <input id="filled-tag-list" type="text" class="form-control js-tag-list" value="fee, fi, fo"/>
    <script>
      GOVUK.Tagging.ready({autocompleteWith: ['fake', 'tag', 'list', 'fee', 'fi', 'fo', 'fum']});
    </script>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

